OL,3,CWhat could the budget mean for Wales?
OL,5,FNewspaper reports at the weekend
OL,6,Fsuggested that the Treasury is still
OL,7,Faiming for a 2p cut but may have to
OL,8,Fsettle for a 1p cut or a change to
OL,9,Fnational insurance instead.
OL,11,FA 1 percentage point cut in the basic
OL,12,Frate from 20 to 19 per cent would mean
OL,13,Fsomeone earning an average salary of
OL,14,Faround #35,000 would see their annual
OL,15,Fincome tax contribution go from #4,486
OL,16,Fto #4,261.70 ` a saving of around
OL,17,F#225. A 2 percentage point cut would
OL,18,Fsee this reduced to #4,037.40.
