OL,5,FCorporation tax, paid by businesses
OL,6,Fwho make more than #250,000 in
OL,7,Fprofits, went up from 19% to 25% in
OL,8,F2023. The Chancellor could look to cut
OL,9,Fthat this year.
OL,11,FHe could also introduce other measures
OL,12,Fthat help businesses such as cutting
OL,13,Femployer national insurance or
OL,14,Fintroducing tax breaks for investing.
OL,16,FUnlike business rates, corporation tax
OL,17,Fis not devolved, so any change would
OL,18,Fdirectly affect businesses here in
OL,19,FWales.
