OL,3,CWhat could the budget mean for Wales?
OL,5,FSecond home owners here in Wales
OL,6,Falready face higher bills as part of
OL,7,Fefforts by the Welsh Government,
OL,8,Fsupported by Plaid Cymru, to prevent
OL,9,Fpeople living in popular coastal and
OL,10,Fcountryside areas.
OL,12,FHoliday let owners now have to pay
OL,13,Fcouncil tax instead of business rates
OL,14,Funless they fill the property for 182
OL,15,Fdays instead of the previous 70 days.
OL,16,FAt the same time, councils here in
OL,17,FWales can charge up to 300% council
OL,18,Ftax for second or empty homes. Most
OL,19,Flocal authorities are imposing the
OL,20,Fcouncil tax premium.
